.:: Einstein-puzzle ::.

There 5 different types of food: mango, tomato, grapes, cucumber, pear
There are 5 different nationalities: british, danish, german, norwegian, swede
There are 5 different favourite beverages: beer, coffee, milk, tea, water
The people's birthday is in 5 different months: march, april, september, january, december
The people use 5 different means of transport: van, quad-bike, snowmobile, car, ship
1. the british is the person eating grapes
2. the swedish is the person driving the snowmobile
3. the danish is the person drinking tea
4. the person eating tomato is on the left of the person eating cucumber
5. the person eating tomato is the person drinking coffee
6. the person who's birthday is in september is the person driving the quad-bike
7. the person eating pear is the person who's birthday is in april
8. the person drinking milk is in the middle
9. the norwegian is on the far left
10. the person who's birthday is in december is on the left or right of the person driving the van
11. the person driving the ships is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in april
12. the person who's birthday is in march is the person drinking beer
13. the german is the person who's birthday is in january
14. the norwegian is on the left or right of the person eating mango
15. the person who's birthday is in december is on the left or right of the person drinking water

.:: Answer ::.
|		|	1	|	2	|	3	|	4	|	5	|
| Food		|    pear	|     mango	|      grapes	|     tomato	|     cucumber	|
| Nationality	|   norwegian	|    danish	|    british	|    german	|    swedish	|
| Transport		|     van	|    ship	|     quad-bike	|     car	|      snowmobile	|
| Beverage	|    water	|     tea	|     milk	|    coffee	|      beer	|
| Birthday		|   april	|    december	|  september	|    january	|   march	|
